# Idea-to-Code Engineering Workflow — Complete Skill Set
### [Organization Name] — Full Process, AI Skills, and Portfolio Planning

This single document consolidates everything built so far: the end-to-end process definition, the full library of stage-agnostic AI skills, and the portfolio-level PI Planning skill. The AI skills are designed to run in any order — each names the artifacts it needs and the artifact it produces, rather than depending on a fixed position in a sequence.

**Every skill in Part 2 ends with a mandatory Self-Verification section** — what it directly confirmed with evidence, what it couldn't verify and why, what it's asserting with some confidence but no hard proof, and what the next skill in the chain should specifically watch for. Review skills use a Verified / Could Not Verify / Confident But Not Proven shape; generation skills use a Grounded / Assumed / Could Not Verify shape, since they're verifying an artifact they just produced rather than claims someone else made. This isn't an optional footer — it's the mechanism that lets downstream skills (and human reviewers) know exactly which parts of an upstream skill's output to trust as-is versus double-check.

`design-doc-generation` also decides whether to produce a Mermaid architecture/flow diagram: required when the change is Medium/High complexity or alters an existing flow, otherwise it asks rather than silently deciding either way.

