## 5. Making It Self-Enforcing in Jira + Confluence

- Add a required **"Risk Tier"** custom field on the Epic. The workflow blocks transition out of "Discovery" status until it's set.
- Create eight Confluence templates: *Vetting Note*, *PRD*, *Idea One-Pager* (Tier 1 lightweight version), *System Impact Map*, *Design Doc* (with the NFR section built in, not optional), *Test Strategy* (test pyramid + NFR verification mapping), *ADR*, *Release Record*. Story creation lives in Jira directly (stories linked to PRD/Design Doc/Test Strategy), not a separate Confluence doc.
- PR template (GitHub/GitLab) requires a Design Doc **and** Test Strategy link for anything Tier 2/3 — make this a checklist item your PR template literally can't be submitted without acknowledging.
- Because every approval is just a Jira status transition or a Confluence page comment with a name and timestamp, **your audit trail falls out of the normal workflow** instead of being a separate compliance exercise. Have your compliance/security team do a one-time mapping of which stage/artifact satisfies which control (e.g., segregation of duties, change approval, retained records) so it's documented once and not re-litigated every audit cycle.

